            <p class="card-text">
              The current population of Greece is a little over 10 million, but
              slowly, the overall population is declining. After hitting a peak
              of 11.1 million in 2010, and slowly ever since, the population has
              been declining every year. This is likely due to the fertility
              rate in Greece greatly decreasing as well. It's projected that the
              population will be down to 6 million by the end of the century.
            </p>
