            <h3 class="card-title">Ethnic Groups</h3>
            <p class="card-text">
              The main Ethnic Groups in Greece are Hellenes also known as
              Greeks, Turks, Albanians, and Bulgarians. However the Hellenes
              make up over 90% of the population. Back in the 4th Century BC,
              Greece was invaded by many different groups of Crusaders, and out
              of those groups, the Slavs created homes and villages in Greece,
              intending to stay forever. However, by the 9th Century BC, most of
              the Slavs had left, leaving only a few to stay. This is when the
              Turks and Albanians arrived to Greece.
            </p>
          </div>
