            <h3 class="card-title">Religion</h3>
            <p class="card-text">
              The main religion practiced in Greece is Greek Orthodox also known
              as Greek Christianity. As of 2015, it was practiced by between
              80-90% of the population primarily in the Greek Orthodox Church.
              The rest of the population primarily are Atheist or Muslim. In the
              past, almost everyone in Greece used to believe in a very
              different religion. They were polytheistic, meaning they believed
              in many Gods and Goddesses with many stories surrounding these
              supernatural beings and the creation of the Universe.
            </p>
          </div>
