            <p class="card-text">
              Greece was home to some of the most influential and famous people
              in all of history. 3 of those people are: <br />
              Alexander the Great: <br />
              Alexander the Great was the king of Greece from 336 BC until his
              death in 323 BC. He was renowned as a God during those times and
              is still considered as a legendary individual to this day.
              <br />
              Homer: <br />
              Homer was a Greek poet who wrote two of the most well known poems
              of all time, The Iliad and The Odyssey. <br />
              Archimedes: <br />
              Archimedes is known as the greatest mathematician, inventor, and
              astronomer of all of the ancient world. He famously created the
              measurements of the circle.
            </p>
